  "prompt": "Where can I get free singing lessons via Skype?",
  "response": "There are several options you can explore to find free singing lessons via Skype:\n\n1. **Online Communities and Forums**: Websites like Reddit (e.g., r/singing) often have members who are willing to offer free lessons in exchange for feedback or just to gain teaching experience.\n\n2. **Social Media Groups**: Platforms like Facebook have groups dedicated to singing or music education. Joining these groups and expressing your interest in free lessons might connect you with someone willing to help.\n\n3. **YouTube Collaborations**: Some YouTube vocal coaches might offer a limited number of free lessons to promote their services. Follow well-known vocal coaches and check their community posts or descriptions for any offers.\n\n4. **Music Schools and Students**: Contact local music schools or universities with music programs. Sometimes, students or instructors offer free lessons as part of their training or outreach initiatives.\n\n5. **Non-Profit Organizations**: Some non-profits or community music programs offer free or subsidized music lessons. They might be willing to schedule lessons over Skype, especially if you're not in their local area.\n\n6. **Online Platforms with Trial Offers**: Services like Udemy, Skillshare, or even private instructors may offer a free trial lesson. While not entirely free, it's a way to get a lesson at no cost initially.\n\nWhen reaching out to potential instructors, make sure to clearly explain your goals and schedule to ensure a good match.",
